cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "humanize — closed-loop, detector-feedback AI-text humanizer"
message: "If you use this software in research, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "humanize contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ssamba1/humanize"
url: "https://github.com/ssamba1/humanize"
abstract: >-
  An open-source, closed-loop AI-text humanizer that iteratively rewrites text against a multi-detector
  ensemble (local proxy detectors plus key-gated commercial APIs) using each detector's score as feedback,
  gated on a semantic-similarity meaning-preservation constraint and byte-for-byte preservation of citations,
  numbers, quotes, and named entities. Packaged as a Claude Code skill and a Python CLI. Research and
  defensive tool.
keywords:
  - ai-humanizer
  - ai-detection
  - detector-feedback
  - text-humanizer
  - nlp
  - claude-skill
license: MIT
